main event: A UFO sighting was reported on 9 June 1966 in Fayetteville, N.C., where multiple lights appeared with a brightness similar to stars, moving straight across the sky and disappearing.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for about 15 minutes, Objects moved from west to east, Witnesses reported seeing two objects traveling in vertical formation and the observations were made without visual aids, The objects had a brightness twice that of average stars and made no sound, All sightings were recorded by personnel from the 464th Troop Carrier Wing, Pope AFB.
sighted object: two bright lights in the sky
witness description: Lt. Robert C. Finley, 1st Lt Carr Wg, and other USAF personnel.
